Build on Windows

Software to install:
- Cygwin
| - gcc
| - make
| - flex
| - bison


Download and compile:
GMP  http://gmplib.org/
MPFR http://mpfr.org/
MPC  http://multiprecision.org/


Preparation:
export PREFIX=$H/opt/cross
export TARGET=i586-elf
export PATH="$PREFIX/bin:$PATH"

Configuration for Binutils:
../binutils-x.y.z/configure --target=$TARGET --prefix="$PREFIX" --disable-nls

Building GCC:
# If you wish to build these packages as part of gcc:
mv gmp-x.y.z gcc-x.y.z/gmp
mv mpfr-x.y.z gcc-x.y.z/mpfr
mv mpc-x.y.z gcc-x.y.z/mpc

mkdir build-gcc
cd build-gcc
../gcc-x.y.z/configure --target=$TARGET --prefix="$PREFIX" --disable-nls --enable-languages=c,c++ --without-headers
make all-gcc
make all-target-libgcc
make install-gcc
make install-target-libgcc

Also, mtools need to be downloaded, compiled and installed.

Troubleshooting:
- set line endings of create-image.sh and mtools.cfg to UNIX
